if you got that impression.

15:28.629 --> 15:30.964
Right.

15:39.773 --> 15:42.075
Let's not
let our hormones

15:42.108 --> 15:44.477
get the better of us.

15:44.511 --> 15:47.981
It hurts, okay?

15:50.016 --> 15:52.352
When you announced
that you were pregnant,

15:52.385 --> 15:55.321
everybody practically jumped
over the table,

15:55.355 --> 15:56.757
but with me--

15:56.790 --> 16:00.360
Well, it is a little more
unexpected with you.

16:00.393 --> 16:02.763
They'll celebrate it.
Just--

16:02.796 --> 16:04.998
Give them time?

16:05.031 --> 16:07.433
You know,

16:07.467 --> 16:11.071
I expected
to raise a few eyebrows

16:11.104 --> 16:13.707
with the people that I--

16:13.740 --> 16:18.712
But...

16:18.745 --> 16:21.281
I guess I consider
the people here

16:21.314 --> 16:23.249
to be like family,

16:23.283 --> 16:25.251
and I didn't think

16:25.285 --> 16:28.354
that I was going to
have to give you all time

16:28.388 --> 16:30.256
to get over it.

16:30.290 --> 16:34.094
Why not just be flush
with happiness

16:34.127 --> 16:38.098
if for no other reason
than because I am?

16:38.131 --> 16:41.034
Ellenor...

16:41.067 --> 16:44.004
you just sprang the news
this morning.

16:46.339 --> 16:49.042
The happiness is there.

16:49.075 --> 16:51.745
Trust me.

17:00.320 --> 17:02.422
What I am saying is
the reason the eyewitness

17:02.455 --> 17:04.223
picked my client
out of a lineup

17:04.257 --> 17:06.291
is because he was shown
a picture of her

17:06.326 --> 17:07.594
by the district attorney.

17:07.627 --> 17:09.395
The witness was identifying

17:09.429 --> 17:12.498
the woman he saw in the store,
not the picture.

17:12.532 --> 17:14.701
We can't know that.
The witness maybe can't know.

17:14.734 --> 17:16.368
He saw a familiar face.
He made--

17:16.402 --> 17:18.739
-Eugene.
-It was improper, Susan.

17:18.771 --> 17:20.272
All right.

17:20.306 --> 17:23.309
This was witness bolstering,
your honor.

17:23.343 --> 17:25.411
First of all,
this wasn't a mug shot.

17:25.444 --> 17:27.814
My client has no record.
There is no mug shot.

17:27.848 --> 17:29.816
The district attorney
took this picture

17:29.850 --> 17:31.552
out of my client's purse.

17:31.585 --> 17:34.254
-I certainly did not.
-Then how'd you get it?

17:34.287 --> 17:37.157
The witness picked it up
off the department store floor.

17:37.190 --> 17:40.126
It fell out of her purse
when she was running away.

17:42.128 --> 17:45.165
The motion to dismiss
is denied.

17:45.198 --> 17:48.669
Let's proceed with the trial.

17:57.310 --> 17:59.513
Perhaps you should have
filled me in

17:59.546 --> 18:01.515
on how they got the picture.

18:01.548 --> 18:03.249
I didn't know.

18:03.283 --> 18:05.719
Get your niece
in here, Harland.

18:05.752 --> 18:07.521
We're going to trial.

18:07.554 --> 18:10.290
Look at the bright side,
Eugene.

18:10.323 --> 18:13.359
I can still get
my jury victory now.

18:13.393 --> 18:17.631
Yes, I'm trying to contain
my delight on that.

18:17.664 --> 18:19.633
I was always close
with my sister.

18:19.666 --> 18:21.635
We were only a year apart.

18:21.668 --> 18:23.637
We were, in many ways,

18:23.670 --> 18:25.639
best friends
as well as siblings.

18:25.672 --> 18:27.674
Did your sister
confide in you

18:27.708 --> 18:29.242
that she was
committing adultery?

18:29.275 --> 18:31.512
Yes. It was I
who convinced her

18:31.545 --> 18:33.680
to be honest and tell Imaad.

18:33.714 --> 18:35.516
I certainly regret
doing that today.

18:35.549 --> 18:36.850
Why is that, sir?

18:36.883 --> 18:38.519
Because he had her killed.

18:38.552 --> 18:40.253
-Objection.
-Sustained.

18:40.286 --> 18:42.488
Mr. McGrath,
did your sister ever talk

18:42.523 --> 18:44.324
about her trip to Pakistan?

18:44.357 --> 18:45.692
Yes, she did.

18:45.726 --> 18:47.260
-Could you tell us--
-Objection-- hearsay.

18:47.293 --> 18:48.529
State of mind.

18:48.562 --> 18:50.396
I'll allow it.

18:50.430 --> 18:52.666
Could you tell us
what she said?

18:52.699 --> 18:54.400
That it was Imaad's idea

18:54.434 --> 18:55.936
as a way of reconnecting.

18:55.969 --> 18:58.805
He thought it would be good
to go back home,

18:58.839 --> 19:00.941
which she thought
was a little bizarre.

19:00.974 --> 19:03.343
Why is that?

19:03.376 --> 19:06.246
He'd always told her,
and me, too, for that matter,

19:06.279 --> 19:07.881
that he didn't enjoy
going home.

19:07.914 --> 19:10.784
He wasn't particularly
close to his family.

19:10.817 --> 19:12.686
Then suddenly she's
going there without him.

19:12.719 --> 19:14.354
Without him?

19:14.387 --> 19:16.790
Out of nowhere, he has this
project he needs to finish,

19:16.823 --> 19:19.459
so he sends her over and says
he'll join her in a few days.

19:19.492 --> 19:21.962
She never suspected he was
sending her to be executed...

19:21.995 --> 19:23.730
-Objection!
-Sustained.

19:23.764 --> 19:26.266
-While he stayed here
as an alibi.
-Objection!

19:26.299 --> 19:28.735
Sustained. Ms. Gamble,
control your witness.

19:28.769 --> 19:30.436
HELEN: Mr. McGrath,

19:30.470 --> 19:33.439
after you learned
of your sister's death,

19:33.473 --> 19:34.808
what happened?

19:34.841 --> 19:36.543
Nothing happened.

19:36.577 --> 19:38.812
The brother confessed,
said it was an honor killing,

19:38.845 --> 19:40.647
and then nothing happened

19:40.681 --> 19:42.583
-because that
son of a bitch...
-BOBBY: Objection!

19:42.616 --> 19:44.484
-He made sure of it.
-Move to strike!

19:44.518 --> 19:46.286
He didn't even go
over there!

19:46.319 --> 19:48.354
I will
have you removed, sir.

19:51.792 --> 19:53.760
Mr. McGrath, please,

19:53.794 --> 19:55.729
you need to calm down.

19:55.762 --> 20:00.667
He didn't even go
over there.

20:00.701 --> 20:03.403
My sister was burned alive.

20:03.436 --> 20:05.471
Nobody did anything.

20:05.506 --> 20:08.341
That's the answer
to your question, Ms. Gamble.

20:08.374 --> 20:10.877
The Pakistani police
did nothing,

20:10.911 --> 20:14.581
our government refuses
to get involved,

20:14.615 --> 20:16.750
and nobody did anything.

20:16.783 --> 20:19.753
A beautiful woman
was murdered,

20:19.786 --> 20:22.022
and nobody did anything.

20:22.055 --> 20:24.424
(sobbing)

20:41.642 --> 20:44.277
My feeling is
they haven't made their case,

20:44.310 --> 20:45.979
but I am concerned.

20:46.012 --> 20:49.616
Their last witness
was extremely emotional.

20:49.650 --> 20:51.685
My gut says put you up there.

20:51.718 --> 20:54.287
Bec?

20:54.320 --> 20:57.057
I think there's no question.
The evidence may be thin,

20:57.090 --> 21:00.060
but they do have phone records
of you calling your brother.

21:00.093 --> 21:02.028
Yes, because I was
about to visit.

21:02.062 --> 21:03.664
People call before--

21:03.697 --> 21:06.299
I'm just saying
it doesn't look good.

21:06.332 --> 21:09.302
It's going to be hard
for the jury to believe

21:09.335 --> 21:11.738
your brother risked
burning your wife openly

21:11.772 --> 21:13.740
without some assurance
of a pardon,

21:13.774 --> 21:15.676
particularly
when the punishment

21:15.709 --> 21:17.343
is death by hanging.

21:17.377 --> 21:19.479
Do you think I'm guilty,
Ms. Washington?

21:19.513 --> 21:20.747
My opinion doesn't matter.

21:20.781 --> 21:22.482
Yeah, well,
I'm taking a poll.

21:24.818 --> 21:27.353
You pardoned the man
that murdered your wife.

21:27.387 --> 21:28.889
Could you kill your sibling?

21:28.922 --> 21:30.657
All right, look,

21:30.691 --> 21:33.694
in your testimony,
I don't know if
it'll be enough

21:33.727 --> 21:35.696
to simply denounce the murder.

21:35.729 --> 21:38.765
You have to condemn the idea
of these honor killings,

21:38.799 --> 21:40.801
and it probably wouldn't hurt

21:40.834 --> 21:44.671
to distance yourself
from your homeland altogether.

21:44.705 --> 21:46.673
I'm an American,
Mr. Donnell,

21:46.707 --> 21:49.409
but I'm also proud
to be Pakistani.

21:49.442 --> 21:52.546
I certainly won't denounce
my native country.

21:52.579 --> 21:54.881
I'm just saying
it wouldn't hurt.

22:03.990 --> 22:06.727
I looked over
and I saw her.

22:06.760 --> 22:09.530
She was stuffing software
into her purse.

22:09.563 --> 22:11.532
You saw this woman?

22:11.565 --> 22:12.599
Yes, ma'am.

22:12.633 --> 22:14.735
And what happened next,
sir?

22:14.768 --> 22:17.470
I started to approach her.
She saw me coming.

22:17.504 --> 22:19.740
She appeared
to know I was suspicious.

22:19.773 --> 22:22.008
All of a sudden,
she just took off.

22:22.042 --> 22:23.544
-She took flight?
-Immediately.

22:23.577 --> 22:25.078
And you couldn't
catch her?

22:25.111 --> 22:27.914
Well, I inadvertently collided
with another customer,

22:27.948 --> 22:32.485
and as a result,
she eluded capture.

22:32.519 --> 22:33.887
Mr. Reddington,

22:33.920 --> 22:36.823
are you absolutely sure
this is the woman you saw

22:36.857 --> 22:38.992
stuffing software
into her purse?

22:39.025 --> 22:40.594
Absolutely.

22:40.627 --> 22:44.598
She's even wearing
the same yellow dress.

22:44.631 --> 22:48.001
She couldn't have come to court
in a different outfit?

22:48.034 --> 22:49.069
Mr. Young?

22:49.102 --> 22:51.104
Yes, your honor.

22:51.137 --> 22:52.438
You're up.

22:52.472 --> 22:54.841
Actually,
my colleague Mr. Bassett

22:54.875 --> 22:57.544
will be conducting cross.

22:57.578 --> 22:59.379
How nice.

23:01.748 --> 23:05.652
Mr. Reddington, are you certain
this is the woman you saw?

23:05.686 --> 23:08.421
-Yes, I am.
-Emma Lugar,

23:08.454 --> 23:10.423
the very woman
you picked out of a lineup?

23:10.456 --> 23:11.925
Correct.

23:11.958 --> 23:14.728
-This is that woman?
You're absolutely sure?
-Yes.

23:14.761 --> 23:17.864
-Positive?
-Objection--
asked and answered.

23:17.898 --> 23:19.199
Sustained.

23:19.232 --> 23:20.500
Nothing further.

23:20.534 --> 23:22.569
The witness
may step down.

23:22.603 --> 23:24.838
Nothing further?

23:24.871 --> 23:26.673
-It went well.
-Went well?

23:26.707 --> 23:28.842
You just got the witness
to confirm the I. D.

23:28.875 --> 23:31.144
three more times.
We represent the defendant.

23:31.177 --> 23:33.580
I realize that.

23:33.614 --> 23:36.517
Mr. Bassett, something
to share with the court?

23:36.550 --> 23:37.951
Yes, your honor.

23:37.984 --> 23:39.953
At this time, I would ask

23:39.986 --> 23:42.756
that the real Emma Lugar
please stand up.

23:45.225 --> 23:48.028
That's the woman charged
with the crime, your honor.

23:48.061 --> 23:51.965
The witness identified
this woman here,

23:51.998 --> 23:55.068
whose name is
Marjorie Hooley.

24:00.574 --> 24:05.846
I will see counsel
in chambers.

24:13.687 --> 24:16.089
Injustice demanded it.

24:16.122 --> 24:19.560
Justice demanded you commit
a fraud on the court?

24:19.593 --> 24:21.628
The lineup was tainted.
As Ms. Lugar's attorney--

24:21.662 --> 24:23.830
-Harland.
-Both of you are
in contempt.

24:23.864 --> 24:25.566
I didn't know.

24:25.599 --> 24:28.168
I told you I would
hold you accountable.

24:28.201 --> 24:29.235
You're in contempt.

24:29.269 --> 24:32.138
You have to declare
a mistrial.

24:32.172 --> 24:35.175
Double jeopardy has been
attached, Ms. Alexander.

24:35.208 --> 24:37.177
She could walk
with a mistrial.

24:37.210 --> 24:40.246
I would suggest you declare
a mistrial on shoplifting,

24:40.280 --> 24:42.248
hold the defendant
in contempt of court,

24:42.282 --> 24:44.651
as well as counsel,
and slap her hard.

24:44.685 --> 24:45.852
That's completely
unethical.

24:45.886 --> 24:47.554
Oh, you're going to
raise ethics?

24:47.588 --> 24:49.089
The defendant followed
the advice of her attorney.

24:49.122 --> 24:50.691
You can't imprison her

24:50.724 --> 24:52.092
for sitting
in the back of a courtroom.

24:52.125 --> 24:54.227
I think we should
just finish the trial

24:54.260 --> 24:56.563
and all learn
from our mistakes.

24:59.866 --> 25:01.935
This is what will happen.

25:01.968 --> 25:05.038
We will put both
of those women at your table,

25:05.071 --> 25:07.841
then allow the witness
to make another I. D.

25:07.874 --> 25:11.277
I will instruct the jury
to disregard the first one.

25:11.311 --> 25:13.614
That will be tantamount
to steering the witness,
your honor.

25:13.647 --> 25:15.882
Mr. Bassett,
the court is not interested

25:15.916 --> 25:18.919
in anything you have to say.

25:18.952 --> 25:20.854
Get those women
at your table.

25:20.887 --> 25:24.858
We will reconvene
after lunch.

25:28.094 --> 25:29.863
The contract looks fine

25:29.896 --> 25:32.633
as between you and
the biological father.

25:32.666 --> 25:34.801
-But?
-Well, you don't have
any authority

25:34.835 --> 25:36.169
to waive the child's rights.

25:36.202 --> 25:38.238
If she wants to sue
for financial support

25:38.271 --> 25:41.241
down the road, you can't
really contract against it.

25:41.274 --> 25:42.909
You didn't think of that?

25:46.012 --> 25:47.013
You got something
to say, Jimmy?

25:47.047 --> 25:48.148
-All right--
-No.

25:48.181 --> 25:49.683
What the hell
did that mean?

25:49.716 --> 25:51.251
-Ell--
-He made a remark,
Lindsay,

25:51.284 --> 25:53.787
and I'm going to
address him on that.

25:53.820 --> 25:55.789
What's your problem,
Jimmy?

25:55.822 --> 25:57.858
Okay.

25:57.891 --> 26:00.794
My problem is
this single mother thing--

26:00.827 --> 26:02.896
more times than not,

26:02.929 --> 26:05.932
I think it's
a selfish thing to do.

26:05.966 --> 26:07.601
Is that right?

26:07.634 --> 26:08.869
Yes.

26:08.902 --> 26:11.171
You're getting a child.
Good for you.

26:11.204 --> 26:12.806
As for the baby,

26:12.839 --> 26:15.241
she's getting a life
with no father.

26:15.275 --> 26:18.078
It's tough enough
growing up these days with--

26:18.111 --> 26:21.014
I'm just saying I don't think
it's any coincidence

26:21.047 --> 26:23.717
when you drew up
that contract there,

26:23.750 --> 26:26.653
you didn't once consider it
from the child's side.

26:26.687 --> 26:29.089
Well, consider this, Jimmy.

26:29.122 --> 26:30.724
Go to hell,

26:30.757 --> 26:32.826
which I know
you believe in,

26:32.859 --> 26:35.195
given the origins
of most of your beliefs.

26:35.228 --> 26:37.263
Fine. Insult me
as a Catholic.

26:37.297 --> 26:39.165
All right, this discussion
isn't necessary.

26:39.199 --> 26:41.735
No, I am insulting you
as a friend,

26:41.768 --> 26:43.770
somebody who I happen
to love

26:43.804 --> 26:46.773
and somebody who I expect
to be there for me--

26:46.807 --> 26:48.308
You know what?

26:48.341 --> 26:50.343
Forget it.

27:04.157 --> 27:07.327
I was horrified
as everybody else.

27:07.360 --> 27:09.429
You didn't know
what he planned to do.

27:09.462 --> 27:11.965
Set my wife on fire?

27:11.998 --> 27:14.234
Of course not.

27:14.267 --> 27:16.870
How did he find out
about your wife's affair?

27:16.903 --> 27:18.304
I told him.

27:18.338 --> 27:22.876
I was very hurt about it,
so I shared my--

27:22.909 --> 27:24.811
What was his reaction?

27:24.845 --> 27:27.247
He was angry, but he certainly
gave me no indication

27:27.280 --> 27:29.249
that he planned
to take her life.

27:29.282 --> 27:31.417
These honor killings--

27:31.451 --> 27:34.154
are they sanctioned
by Islamic law?

27:34.187 --> 27:36.256
No, nor are they
by Pakistani law.

27:36.289 --> 27:38.725
It's simply a custom,
an ancient one,

27:38.759 --> 27:40.727
which is
hardly ever practiced.

27:40.761 --> 27:43.363
The question becomes
your brother.

27:43.396 --> 27:45.999
Did you know
that he believed

27:46.032 --> 27:47.968
in honor killings?

27:48.001 --> 27:50.436
No. It was nothing
we ever talked about.

27:50.470 --> 27:52.072
He's an educated man.

27:52.105 --> 27:55.776
He burned your wife.

27:57.477 --> 28:01.014
Yes.

28:01.047 --> 28:03.750
And you pardoned him.

28:11.257 --> 28:12.859
Because he's my brother.

28:15.428 --> 28:19.800
I know his heart, and...

28:19.833 --> 28:24.104
if I didn't,
he would have been hanged.

28:24.137 --> 28:26.272
As much as I hate him
for what he did--

28:26.306 --> 28:27.741
as much as I--

28:27.774 --> 28:30.310
I will never
be able to forgive him,

28:30.343 --> 28:34.147
I couldn't sign
his death warrant.

28:38.919 --> 28:40.420
Your brother decides
to redeem you

28:40.453 --> 28:41.988
by burning your spouse alive.

28:42.022 --> 28:43.890
He doesn't check
with you first

28:43.924 --> 28:45.425
to say,
"Hey, do you mind?"

28:45.458 --> 28:47.260
He knew I would have
stopped him.

28:47.293 --> 28:48.494
Did he know
you'd pardon him?

28:48.529 --> 28:50.230
No.

28:50.263 --> 28:52.332
He commits murder
in front of a lot of witnesses

28:52.365 --> 28:54.267
-with no assurance
that you'd--
-That's right.

28:54.300 --> 28:55.902
Where is he now,
Mr. Sharif?

28:55.936 --> 28:57.337
He's in Pakistan.

28:57.370 --> 28:59.339
So he'll burn a woman
to preserve your honor,

28:59.372 --> 29:00.541
but he can't get on a plane

29:00.574 --> 29:02.375
and come testify
on your behalf?

29:02.408 --> 29:05.111
If he came to this country,
he'd be jailed for life.

29:05.145 --> 29:07.447
So he's letting you
take the fall.

29:07.480 --> 29:09.883
He kills the wife,
you take the rap.

29:09.916 --> 29:13.353
Getting convicted of murder--
that's not a dishonor to you?

29:13.386 --> 29:15.522
In your country,
it's not a disgrace

29:15.556 --> 29:17.423
-to be a convicted murderer?
-Objection.

29:17.457 --> 29:19.159
Overruled.

29:19.192 --> 29:20.561
How about simply
committing murder?

29:20.594 --> 29:22.262
Any dishonor in that?

29:22.295 --> 29:24.197
Your brother is even a hero
over there, isn't he?

29:24.230 --> 29:25.999
BOBBY: Objection--
what's the relevance?

29:26.032 --> 29:27.901
The relevance is
this is win/win.

29:27.934 --> 29:29.903
One brother gets rid
of a wife

29:29.936 --> 29:32.839
while the other one gets
to enjoy a hero's status.

29:32.873 --> 29:35.942
-Objection. Move to strike.
-I don't consider
my brother a hero.

29:35.976 --> 29:37.844
The objection
is sustained.

29:37.878 --> 29:40.213
Mr. Sharif,
is it your testimony

29:40.246 --> 29:42.282
that, knowing
Pakistani culture,

29:42.315 --> 29:44.284
it wasn't at all foreseeable

29:44.317 --> 29:47.287
that your brother might attempt
to kill your wife?

29:47.320 --> 29:49.322
Murder is not part
of Pakistani culture,

29:49.355 --> 29:50.557
Ms. Gamble.

29:50.591 --> 29:52.125
Wait a second.

29:52.158 --> 29:54.227
We're here today
because a man's honor

29:54.260 --> 29:56.362
has been placed
above a woman's life.

29:56.396 --> 29:58.164
It's an ancient custom.

29:58.198 --> 30:00.433
It doesn't reflect
today's practice.

30:00.466 --> 30:02.536
Mr. Sharif,
are little girls used

30:02.569 --> 30:04.571
to settle disputes
in Pakistan?

30:04.605 --> 30:08.008
Again, you're talking
about an archaic custom.

30:08.041 --> 30:09.943
Practiced by the same people

30:09.976 --> 30:11.845
that commit
these honor killings.

30:11.878 --> 30:14.380
Objection--
this is so far off track.

30:14.414 --> 30:16.382
Sustained. Keep it
about the case, Ms. Gamble.

30:16.416 --> 30:18.318
This is about the case,
your honor.

30:18.351 --> 30:20.486
He knew where
he was sending his wife

30:20.521 --> 30:22.956
and he knew
what would happen to her.

30:22.989 --> 30:25.225
-Objection.
-Sustained.

30:25.258 --> 30:28.128
Mr. Sharif, did you call
your brother from the airport

30:28.161 --> 30:30.130
the day your wife flew out?

30:30.163 --> 30:32.298
-Yes, but I was--
-And you called him again

30:32.332 --> 30:35.468
the same day your wife
was set on fire, didn't you?

30:35.501 --> 30:39.372
With respect to my trip.

30:43.243 --> 30:46.279
With respect to your trip.

30:49.215 --> 30:52.085
I have nothing further.

31:10.937 --> 31:12.673
I didn't really think it was
an illegal thing to do.

31:12.706 --> 31:14.675
Then why didn't you tell me
you planned to do it?

31:14.708 --> 31:17.077
Well, I knew it was dicey
and I didn't want

31:17.110 --> 31:19.045
-to get your hands dirty.
-Didn't want me
to get my hands dirty?

31:19.079 --> 31:20.614
My hands are
all over this, Harland.

31:20.647 --> 31:22.215
-Eugene--
-I'm here as a favor to you.

31:22.248 --> 31:23.650
You walk into my office,

31:23.684 --> 31:25.118
ask for my help,
and this is what you do?

31:25.151 --> 31:27.320
Now, you may not care
about your reputation,

31:27.353 --> 31:29.322
but I damn well care
about mine,

31:29.355 --> 31:31.424
and sitting
at the same table with you

31:31.457 --> 31:33.426
hurts my reputation.
Can you understand that?

31:33.459 --> 31:37.363
You did that to me
in there.

31:37.397 --> 31:40.967
That wasn't my intent.

31:44.337 --> 31:47.007
See this briefcase, Eugene?

31:47.040 --> 31:50.644
It's my office.

31:50.677 --> 31:53.479
I got evicted from--

31:53.514 --> 31:58.151
Hard to make a rent
when you can't get a client.

31:58.184 --> 31:59.720
And you think
acting like a buffoon

31:59.753 --> 32:00.987
will get you clients?

32:01.021 --> 32:03.223
I think if I can get
one victory

32:03.256 --> 32:06.226
and I can stop having
to advise potential clients

32:06.259 --> 32:07.961
that I've never--

32:07.994 --> 32:10.263
It was worth
risking contempt!

32:16.036 --> 32:18.639
When this case is over,

32:18.672 --> 32:21.241
don't you ever,

32:21.274 --> 32:24.945
ever come to see me again.

32:27.714 --> 32:29.415
You got that?

32:31.685 --> 32:33.620
Got it.

32:49.135 --> 32:51.538
Did I miss something?

32:51.572 --> 32:53.540
Did you?

32:53.574 --> 32:56.577
The commonwealth put no evidence
of any conversation

32:56.610 --> 32:59.279
between my client
and his brother

32:59.312 --> 33:02.382
concerning the death
of Julie McGrath--

33:02.415 --> 33:04.551
no evidence of any planning,
any aid,

33:04.585 --> 33:06.553
no evidence whatsoever

33:06.587 --> 33:09.155
that my client knew
it was going to happen.

33:09.189 --> 33:11.758
The prosecution's
entire case is,

33:11.792 --> 33:14.394
"Gee, they were brothers.
He must have known."

33:14.427 --> 33:16.362
That's it.

33:16.396 --> 33:21.501
Imaad Sharif is on trial here
only out of frustration.

33:21.535 --> 33:25.506
They can't get
the real killer.

33:25.539 --> 33:29.643
A sympathetic family
sits over there wanting justice.

33:29.676 --> 33:34.047
A frustrated district attorney
wants somebody to pay,

33:34.080 --> 33:37.083
so it's,
"Let's nail the brother."

33:39.085 --> 33:41.487
You know, usually I find myself
standing up here

33:41.522 --> 33:44.791
asking juries
to analyze the evidence...

33:44.825 --> 33:50.795
find not guilty
beyond reasonable doubt.

33:51.698 --> 33:57.270
Here, there is no evidence.

33:57.303 --> 34:00.106
None.

34:02.576 --> 34:04.611
HELEN:
You want evidence?

34:04.645 --> 34:07.413
A wife cheats on her husband.

34:07.447 --> 34:10.283
Suddenly, he plans a trip
to Pakistan.

34:10.315 --> 34:13.554
He sends her off alone.

34:13.587 --> 34:15.188
His brother kills her

34:15.221 --> 34:17.558
while he sits comfortably
in the United States

34:17.591 --> 34:19.425
with an alibi.

34:19.458 --> 34:24.831
Then,
pursuant to Pakistani law,
he grants a pardon,

34:24.864 --> 34:29.101
and his brother completely
gets away with it.

34:29.135 --> 34:34.841
Yes, it's a little
frustrating.

34:34.875 --> 34:37.578
The murderer falls back
on Pakistani law

34:37.610 --> 34:42.215
where this tribal qisas thing
can get him off,

34:42.248 --> 34:47.588
while the conspiring husband
relies on American courts

34:47.621 --> 34:52.458
and takes advantage of
our higher burdens of proof.

34:52.492 --> 34:54.860
This man comes from a society

34:54.895 --> 34:58.331
that treats women
as commodities,

34:58.364 --> 35:01.602
a nation that burns
bad wives.

35:01.635 --> 35:04.838
In America, we don't do that.

35:04.871 --> 35:07.207
We don't condone
honor killings.

35:07.240 --> 35:11.612
We don't consider any murder
to be honorable.

35:11.645 --> 35:14.615
You all know what he did.

35:14.648 --> 35:19.620
Come back with a verdict
which reminds him

35:19.653 --> 35:22.656
what country he is in now.

35:31.632 --> 35:34.234
REDDINGTON:
And as I said before,

35:34.267 --> 35:36.603
as she saw me coming,
she took off.

35:36.637 --> 35:38.238
I continued pursuit,

35:38.271 --> 35:40.607
but after colliding
with another customer,

35:40.641 --> 35:42.242
she got away.

35:42.275 --> 35:44.878
And, Mr. Reddington,
one more time,

35:44.911 --> 35:47.280
I would ask you
to identify for the court

35:47.313 --> 35:50.617
the woman you saw
in the store that day.

35:50.651 --> 35:53.319
She's sitting right there
in the blue dress.

35:54.688 --> 35:58.892
Mr. Reddington, I'd like
you to look closely.

35:58.925 --> 36:01.728
Are you sure the woman
in the blue dress is the one?

36:01.762 --> 36:02.929
Absolutely.

36:02.963 --> 36:05.732
Sir, one more time.

36:05.766 --> 36:06.933
Objection.

36:06.967 --> 36:08.735
That's her in the blue dress.

36:08.769 --> 36:10.470
Are you sure
it wasn't me?

36:11.838 --> 36:16.476
I'm directing a verdict
of not guilty.

36:16.510 --> 36:18.779
Ms. Lugar,
you are free to go,

36:18.812 --> 36:20.747
as are you,
Ms. Blue dress.

36:20.781 --> 36:22.348
I don't even know
your name.

36:22.382 --> 36:24.918
Bailiff, take Mr. Bassett
into custody.

36:24.951 --> 36:28.522
Mr. Bassett, I sentence you
to 15 days in lockup

36:28.555 --> 36:29.923
for contempt of court,

36:29.956 --> 36:31.558
sentence to begin
immediately.

36:31.592 --> 36:34.260
(bangs gavel)

36:34.294 --> 36:35.629
We won.

36:35.662 --> 36:37.263
Yes, we did.

36:37.297 --> 36:38.632
This counts.

36:38.665 --> 36:40.934
It's a jury trial.

36:40.967 --> 36:43.303
It counts.

36:45.271 --> 36:47.908
Thank you, Eugene.

36:49.610 --> 36:51.344
Sure.

37:16.503 --> 37:19.640
The truth is,
I do have a problem

37:19.673 --> 37:24.645
with the single mother thing
as an ideal, like I said.

37:24.678 --> 37:29.015
The truth is I do
consider us like family,

37:29.049 --> 37:32.686
and family members
judge each other all the time.

37:32.719 --> 37:35.756
We're always
in each other's business.

37:35.789 --> 37:38.491
I took the liberty
of butting into yours

37:38.525 --> 37:42.495
because I do care
about you, Ellenor.

37:42.529 --> 37:46.032
You're like a sister to me,

37:46.066 --> 37:50.036
and while I may have doubts
about what you're doing,

37:50.070 --> 37:52.338
there should be no doubt

37:52.372 --> 37:57.343
that I will be there for you
every step,

37:57.377 --> 38:00.514
whatever you need.

38:00.547 --> 38:04.785
I know that, Jimmy,

38:04.818 --> 38:07.287
and I appreciate that.

38:09.923 --> 38:12.626
I wish you could see

38:12.659 --> 38:16.362
what I need right now

38:16.396 --> 38:19.399
is for you
to share in my joy.

38:43.857 --> 38:46.593
KITTELSON:
Mr. Sharif, please rise.

38:48.028 --> 38:50.531
Has the jury reached
a verdict?

38:50.564 --> 38:52.633
We have, your honor.

38:52.666 --> 38:54.100
What say you?

38:54.134 --> 38:57.370
Commonwealth
vs. Imaad Sharif,

38:57.403 --> 38:58.905
count one on the charge

38:58.939 --> 39:01.074
of accessory before the fact
to murder--

39:01.107 --> 39:03.977
we find the defendant
Imaad Sharif...

39:04.010 --> 39:05.846
guilty.

39:05.879 --> 39:08.749
Count two, on the charge

39:08.782 --> 39:10.584
of conspiracy
to commit murder,

39:10.617 --> 39:13.486
we find the defendant
Imaad Sharif...

39:13.520 --> 39:15.488
guilty.

39:21.862 --> 39:24.464
Ask the court enter
findings of not guilty

39:24.497 --> 39:26.667
of both counts,
notwithstanding the verdict.

39:26.700 --> 39:28.935
Denied. Security, take
the defendant into custody.

39:28.969 --> 39:32.105
We'll schedule sentencing
later.

39:32.138 --> 39:34.575
Members of the jury,
thank you for your service.

39:34.608 --> 39:36.543
We are adjourned.

39:47.888 --> 39:50.857
I need a second.

39:50.891 --> 39:52.859
Ex parte, counsel.

39:52.893 --> 39:55.428
Oh, we're suddenly
going to exalt the law?

39:55.461 --> 39:56.963
It would be
a big mistake

39:56.997 --> 40:00.601
for you to come in here
and insult me.

40:00.634 --> 40:03.136
Well, this seems to be
the day for big mistakes.

40:03.169 --> 40:04.871
There was no basis
for that verdict,

40:04.905 --> 40:06.072
and you know it.
It was totally--

40:06.106 --> 40:08.575
You're going to tell me
what I know?

40:08.609 --> 40:10.210
Let me tell you
what I know.

40:10.243 --> 40:13.213
I've always known you to be
a judge who's about the law,

40:13.246 --> 40:15.849
despite all the wacky stuff
you got going on.

40:15.882 --> 40:17.718
When you put that robe on,
you've always been a judge--

40:17.751 --> 40:20.086
a good one, a fair one.

40:20.120 --> 40:21.221
You pride yourself on that.

40:21.254 --> 40:23.123
Where the hell was
your pride today?

40:23.156 --> 40:25.491
The district attorney
delivered

40:25.526 --> 40:27.861
one of the most bigoted
closings I've ever seen,

40:27.894 --> 40:29.596
and you didn't blink.

40:29.630 --> 40:31.865
The prejudice in this trial
has been screaming!

40:31.898 --> 40:33.499
And the loudest scream

40:33.534 --> 40:35.501
came in the form
of that verdict.

40:35.536 --> 40:38.772
How in God's name
can you let it stand?

40:38.805 --> 40:43.510
For the record, counsel,
what you call bigotry

40:43.544 --> 40:45.512
the district attorney
calls motive,

40:45.546 --> 40:47.948
and she is free
to argue that.

40:47.981 --> 40:50.717
Second,
circumstantial evidence

40:50.751 --> 40:52.953
is enough to convict,

40:52.986 --> 40:56.690
and this jury found
that evidence to be compelling.

40:56.723 --> 41:01.795
It is not my function
to substitute my judgment.

41:01.828 --> 41:05.231
And lastly,
off the record,

41:05.265 --> 41:10.537
any man whose brother
burns women alive--

41:10.571 --> 41:12.539
he can't be all good.

41:12.573 --> 41:15.241
Now please leave.

41:15.275 --> 41:18.979
Wow.

41:19.012 --> 41:20.547
I guess prejudice

41:20.581 --> 41:25.218
is cloaked in black robes
sometimes, too.

41:25.251 --> 41:27.220
I asked you to leave,

41:27.253 --> 41:31.925
and you would be wise
to do so now.

41:37.263 --> 41:39.633
(door slams)

41:48.642 --> 41:50.043
Hey, Eugene.

41:50.076 --> 41:51.645
Hey.

41:54.648 --> 41:56.049
You doing okay?

41:56.082 --> 41:58.619
Oh, sure.

41:58.652 --> 42:01.054
They took away my tie,
my shoelaces,

42:01.087 --> 42:03.624
like I'm going to
hang myself or something.

42:03.657 --> 42:05.058
Believe that?

42:05.091 --> 42:07.060
On this day,
coming off a victory?

42:07.093 --> 42:08.595
Yeah, right.

42:08.629 --> 42:13.266
It was a victory.
You realize that?

42:13.299 --> 42:15.301
Oh, of course I do.

42:18.138 --> 42:20.841
I want to apologize
for humiliating you.

42:20.874 --> 42:23.109
I never meant to.

42:23.143 --> 42:26.012
Ahh, I know.

42:26.046 --> 42:28.582
The insurance company

42:28.615 --> 42:30.951
has to lift
that mandate now.

42:30.984 --> 42:33.954
No more having to warn clients
you've never won.

42:33.987 --> 42:35.589
Yeah.

42:35.622 --> 42:37.357
It's a start.

42:37.390 --> 42:39.960
You take the victory,
you enjoy it,

42:39.993 --> 42:42.663
then you build on it.

42:42.696 --> 42:44.030
Oh, I will.

42:44.064 --> 42:47.133
I'm just sitting here
savoring the moment.

42:47.167 --> 42:51.872
Nobody has to be
worrying about me anymore.

42:51.905 --> 42:54.207
Good.

42:54.240 --> 42:57.711
Thanks, Eugene.

42:57.744 --> 43:00.213
Sure thing.

43:00.246 --> 43:01.982
Night, Harland.

43:02.015 --> 43:04.017
Night.

